title: For Sale:  Performance Center Shield 9mm FS/FT
postcontent: I bought this Shield in late winter and ran about 4 boxes of ammo through it. It is the Performance Center model with large fiber optic sights, a ported barrel and slide, and an Apex sear.($40)The trigger is absolutely great. Crisp break, light pull (~5 lbs) and short reset. With the ported barrel and light bullets, I can shoot it just as fast and accurate as my full size M&P at 7 yards (~.16-.17 second splits)However, I am an expert pistol shot and this Performance Center Shield is not accurate enough for me. With my buddy's normal Shield, I did a 9 shot 25 yard group of about 2.5 inches. This gun won't do better than 6 inches at 25 yards. It is far more likely that I will use my ccw on a coyote or small game than anything else, and this shield is not rabbit accurate at 25 yards. That is the full disclosure on why I want to get another gun, and I imagine that it won't be a deal breaker for many people because I am an oddball who shoots small game with a ccw handgun.Anyways, I am looking to sell outright for $440 or trade for another 9mm Shield + cash on your end. The PC model and the sear put this at about $140 more than a standard Shield. Text or voicemail at 33030751ohfive
